g.text: UML Diagram: Class Notation in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.

a.title: ― TypedString: TypedString combines a type with content defined as a simple string. May be used wherever a simple string needs to support a type definition to clarify its content.
a.xlink:title: ― TypedString: TypedString combines a type with content defined as a simple string. May be used wherever a simple string needs to support a type definition to clarify its content.

a.title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.
a.xlink:title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.

a.title: ― WhiteSpaceRule: WhiteSpace constrains the value space of types derived from string.
a.xlink:title: ― WhiteSpaceRule: WhiteSpace constrains the value space of types derived from string.

a.title: ― ClassificationItem: A space for a category within a statistical classification.
a.xlink:title: ― ClassificationItem: A space for a category within a statistical classification.

a.title: ― Code: The characters used as a symbol to designate a category within a codelist or classification. (Formally, a sign for which the signifier is non-linguistic alphanumeric string.)
a.xlink:title: ― Code: The characters used as a symbol to designate a category within a codelist or classification. (Formally, a sign for which the signifier is non-linguistic alphanumeric string.)

a.title: ― Datum: Correspondence of a data instance to the concept it represents.
a.xlink:title: ― Datum: Correspondence of a data instance to the concept it represents.

a.title: ― Category: Concept whose role is to define and measure a characteristic.
a.xlink:title: ― Category: Concept whose role is to define and measure a characteristic.

a.title: ― Signifier: Concept whose extension includes perceivable objects.
a.xlink:title: ― Signifier: Concept whose extension includes perceivable objects.

a.title: ― represents: Notation represents zero to many categories.
a.xlink:title: ― represents: Notation represents zero to many categories.

a.title: ― uses: Classification item uses a notation.
a.xlink:title: ― uses: Classification item uses a notation.
